      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COLOURS OF AUTUMN (3) resumed at Townsville over 1000m at this level, beaten only 1.75 lengths. It was a tough effort after settling back from an awkward gate. She has plenty up her sleeve and has won 3/5 second up. Fitter and draws inside today. Rates the one to beat. MATERIALIST (4) is racing well and is close to another win. Has been cruelled by wide gates and may be able to sit closer today. Best figures measure up right up, and she's sure to run well. KIRIKAN (6) hasn't won for a long while, but he went close numerous times last preparation and resumed with a nose defeat over 1200m at Townsville. Drew 11 in that and charged home. Has the rail today and Wiggins sticking aboard is a positive push for his chances. CHARTWELL (1) mixes the form but peaks for this and would be around the mark bringing his A-game.",
